The paper focuses on artificial intelligence and robotic grasping methods, which are typically studied in the robotics sub-category (cs.RO). The use of visual semantic attributes and knowledge base graph representation suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation metrics and zero-shot affordance prediction scenario suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
